                                109 Natural Gas Powered Trucks Now Serving Puget Sound 
            


            November 4, 2014
        



















        Republic's CNG-powered waste/recycle trucks on the job in Puget Sound, Washington.
        





Republic Services has announced the addition of 14 new Compressed Natural Gas (CNG) solid waste and recycling trucks to serve customers throughout the greater Eastside, Puget Sound, Washington. This addition brings the total number of CNG trucks operated by Republic in the greater Puget Sound area to 109. The new CNG trucks replace older diesel-powered trucks, and represent a significant local investment in cleaner, safer and more efficient vehicles.

